  <notes>
    <note date="2026-02-04">
      Implemented card click navigation for DueDatesWidget:

      **New File Created:**
      - `src/client/pcf/DueDatesWidget/control/services/navigationService.ts`

      **Files Updated:**
      - `src/client/pcf/DueDatesWidget/control/components/EventListItem.tsx` - Added loading state support
      - `src/client/pcf/DueDatesWidget/control/components/DueDatesWidgetRoot.tsx` - Integrated navigation service

      **Implementation Details:**

      1. **Navigation Service** (`navigationService.ts`):
         - `navigateToEvent()` - Main function to navigate to Events tab + open side pane
         - `navigateToEventsPage()` - For "All Events" link (Task 055)
         - `navigateToEventsTab()` - Internal helper for tab navigation
         - `closeEventDetailPane()`, `isEventDetailPaneOpen()` - Pane utilities
         - Uses same side pane ID and Custom Page name as Task 031 (sidePaneUtils.ts)
         - Graceful fallback when APIs not available (test harness compatibility)

      2. **Tab Navigation Logic**:
         - Searches for Events tab by common names: events, Events, eventsTab, tab_events, sprk_events
         - Falls back to iterating tabs looking for "event" in name
         - Makes hidden tabs visible before focusing

      3. **Side Pane Opening**:
         - Reuses existing pane if open (per Task 031 pattern)
         - Creates new pane if not open (400px width, closeable)
         - Passes eventId and eventType via URL query parameters

      4. **Loading State**:
         - `isNavigating` prop added to EventListItem
         - Shows spinner next to days-until-due badge while loading
         - Reduces opacity and disables interaction during navigation
         - Prevents double-click issues

      5. **Keyboard Navigation**:
         - Already implemented in EventListItem (Enter/Space keys)
         - Added aria-busy and aria-disabled for accessibility
         - tabIndex set to -1 while navigating

      6. **Error Handling**:
         - Partial success support (tab navigation only if side pane fails)
         - User-friendly error messages
         - Navigation errors shown in state (navigationError)

      **Build Status:** Successfully compiles with `npm run build`
    </note>
  </notes>
